    "sections": {
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload the plugin files to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory, or install the plugin through the WordPress plugins screen directly (if available).</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; screen in WordPress</li>\n<li>Add the block from the inserter within the WordPress editor.</li>\n<li>If necessary, add CSS variables using .theme-dark to assign dark mode colors. <a href=\"https://rich.blog/dark-mode-toggle-block/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Learn more</a></li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<dt id='can%20the%20dark%20mode%20toggle%20block%20be%20used%20with%20my%20theme%3F'>\nCan the Dark Mode Toggle block be used with my theme?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes! You will need to add CSS variables to map existing coor values to a dark style though. <a href=\"https://rich.blog/dark-mode-toggle-block/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Learn more</a>.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id='where%20can%20i%20send%20feedback%20or%20ideas%3F'>\nWhere can I send feedback or ideas?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Please reach out via the official <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/dark-mode-toggle-block\" rel=\"ugc\">plugin support forum</a>.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id='where%20can%20i%20find%20the%20development%20files%3F'>\nWhere can I find the development files?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>You can find the development files for the block on <a href=\"https://github.com/richtabor/dark-mode-toggle-block\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">GitHub</a>.</p>\n</p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.0.4</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improve default colors.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.3</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update readme.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Improve block example.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update prefix.</li>\n<li>Improve inline script.</li>\n<li>Use apiVersion 3.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release.</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "description": "<p>A WordPress block for toggling between between light and dark appearance on your site.</p>\n"
    },
